#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Let's think about what happened in this story."
msgstr "Hebu tufikirie kuhusu kilichotokea kwenye Hadithi hii."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Why did giving a consequence this way not work well?"
msgstr "Je, kwa nini amri ya kufanya athari kwa njia hii haikufanikiwa vizuri?"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "The consequence was too strong"
msgstr "Athari ilikuwa ngumu mno"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, a strong reaction like that just made everyone more angry and upset."
msgstr "Ndiyo, mwitikio mkubwa kama huo ulimfanya kila mtu kukasirika zaidi na kusikitika."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No gadget use the next day"
msgstr "Hakuna kutumia vifaa vya kielektroniki siku inayofuata"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Write a letter of apology"
msgstr "Kuandika barua ya kuomba msamaha"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Cannot see friends the next day"
msgstr "Haruhusiwi kuwatembelea marafiki siku inayofuata"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Cannot play with phone after dinner (or next hour)"
msgstr "Haruhusiwi kuchezea simu baada ya chakula cha usiku (au saa inayofuata)"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Take 5 minutes' pause in a separate part of the room"
msgstr "Kutulia kwa dakika 5 ukiwa upande mwingine wa chumba"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Extra time with phone after dinner (30 min)"
msgstr "Muda wa ziada akiwa na simu baada ya chakula cha usiku (dakika 30)"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Extra one-on-one time on Sunday (30 min)"
msgstr "Muda wa ziada wa kuzungumza wawili Jumapili (dakika 30)"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "EXPLAIN"
msgstr "ELEZA"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Check you are both calm. Take a few breaths. Explain to your teen why you are concerned about their behaviour.\n"
"\n"
"Explain the reasons why the rule mattered. You can share your feelings – it is okay to say you are disappointed."
msgstr ""
"Hakikisha nyote wawili mmetulia. Vuta pumzi mara kadhaa. Mweleze kijana wako kwa nini una wasiwasi na tabia zake.\n"
"\n"
"Eleza kwa nini sheria hiyo ilikuwa muhimu. Unaweza kumshirikisha hisia zako – si vibaya kusema umesikitika."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "AGREE"
msgstr "KUBALI"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Plan consequences with your teen for following and not following the rule.\n"
"\n"
"Ask for their ideas. Talk until you agree on something realistic.\n"
"\n"
"Make a consequence for NOT following the rule and a privilege when they DO follow the rule."
msgstr ""
"Panga na kijana wako athari za kufuata sheria na kutofuata sheria.\n"
"\n"
"Mwombe atoe maoni yake. Zungumzeni hadi mtakapokubaliana kuhusu kitu halisi.\n"
"\n"
"Weka athari za KUTOFUATA sheria na upendeleo pindi WANAPOFUATA sheria."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "ACT"
msgstr "TENDA"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Let's think about this story."
msgstr "Hebu tufikirie kuhusu hadithi hii."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Why did using a consequence work well this time?"
msgstr "Kwa nini amri ya kufanya athari ilifanikiwa vizuri mara hii?"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "They agreed on consequences together"
msgstr "Walikubaliana pamoja kuhusu athari"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "The consequence was realistic and appropriate"
msgstr "Athari ziikuwa sahihi na zinazotekelezeka"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Not seeing any friends for a month"
msgstr "Hakuna kumtembelea rafiki yeyote kwa mwezi mmoja"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No TV this evening"
msgstr "Hakuna kuangalia runinga jioni ya leo"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes"
msgstr "Ndiyo"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No"
msgstr "Hapana"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"My mom and dad would always punish me when they were angry with me. They would shout at me and I would also get angry. I often did not follow the rules, because they were too harsh, I did not understand what they were saying, or I would not even bother listening to them, because we were all angry.\n"
"\n"
"One day, they asked me: Let's think together what the consequence should be for not coming home in time. It was great to give my view – before something happens that makes us all angry. We are all calm and agree first. It is easier for me to follow the rules now because I know I agreed on the rule and on the consequence if I do not follow the rule."
msgstr ""
"Mama na Baba yangu mara nyingi waliniadhibu pindi walipokuwa na hasira na mimi. Walinifokea na mimi nilipata hasira. Mara nyingi sikufuata sheria zao, kwa sababu zilikuwa kali, sikuelewa kile walichokuwa wakisema, au Nilikuwa sijihangaishi kuwasikiliza, kwa sababu wote tulikuwa na hasira.\n"
"\n"
"Siku moja, waliniuliza: Hebu tufikiri kwa pamoja madhara yanayoweza kukupata kwa kushindwa kurudi nyumbani kwa wakati. Ilikuwa ni furaha kubwa kutoa maoni yangu kabla kitu hakijatokea na kutufanya wote kuwa na hasira. Wote tulitulia na kukubaliana kwanza. Sasa ni rahisi kwangu kufuata sheria kwa sababu najua na nilikubali sheria hizo na madhara kama sitafuata sheria hizo."

